<br>
What VI didn't do was make sure that any race benefits/penalties didn't get compromised by upgrades to gear/abilities as the game progressed. The races do have differences, but 3 expansions have made almost all those differences null and void. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uraunstoncutter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 134<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/26/02 10:33:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1963.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Race Should Matter</span><hr size=1> Race does matter.  My point is my fascination with SK's.<br>
1st sk twink:  oggie, deleted at lvl 16, back to dorf warrior main<br>
2ed SK twink:  Iksar, deleted at lvl 16, back to dorf warrior.<br>
3rd SK twink:  Human, liking much more than others, lvl 11 so far.<br>
<br>
Now this might seem pretty sad, that so far I have 43 lvls of SK invested into 3 characters.  Ok, it IS sad.  But I deleted my frist 2 based entirly on the factthat I grew to hate their race/looks.  Sure, oggies in old models were damn cute, but my sense of speed and movement sucked.  Plus lookind down to fight annoyed me.  Iksar's were sure seksi!  but again, I grew to hate their looping gait(sp?), and their movements.<br>
<br>
Now I'm with the human, I like the way he looks in armor, his animations, and his &quot;character&quot; better than the other two.  Sure, I can blame it on concepts, but the race of human is working for me here.<br>
<br>
race matters to the player, not really to the game that much.  And that's fine with me. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter 56 Warrior</a>
